<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.ITextureBuffer.SetDataPersistenceFlags" Title="SetDataPersistenceFlags method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.ITextureBuffer">ITextureBuffer</PageRef> ->
    SetDataPersistenceFlags
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>SetDataPersistenceFlags</TypeRef> method provides hints to the renderer about the required lifetime of existing texture data.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[void SetDataPersistenceFlags(DataPersistenceFlags dataPersistenceFlags);]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Argument list">
      <ArgumentList>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="DataPersistenceFlags" Name="dataPersistenceFlags">
          The persistence flags that describe when existing resource data may be discarded.
        </ArgumentListEntry>
      </ArgumentList>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
